The paper deals with remote sensing images and proposes a method based on convolutional neural network (CNN) and deep forest for cloud detection. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning models such as CNN and the mention of structured forests indicate that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The segmentation of images into super-pixels and the use of a distance metric suggest that the paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of remote sensing images and the focus on cloud detection suggest that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
